The Pakistan Electronic Media Regulatory Authority (Pemra) has prohibited the broadcast of advertisements produced in India or featuring Indian actors and characters. In a communiqué sent to all of its television and radio licensees, the regulator said that it had withdrawn the permission for airing Indian channels and content on the directions of the Supreme Court in October last year. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network “However, it has been observed that advertisements of various products of multinationals which are either produced in India or carrying Indian characters/talents are being aired on electronic media,” said the letter shared on Pemra’s official Twitter account.